Jarrod Friedman has been appointed CFO and executive director of enX Group, effective September 1. Friedman served as CFO of enX from April 2013 to April 2016, following which he was appointed to 3G Mobile as group CFO until its recent sale to Blue Label Telecoms. “We are very pleased to have a person of Jarrod’s calibre back at enX to assist the group in executing its strategy,” CEO Steven Joffe said in a statement.